# ERP Report Designer — Visual Template Standard

## Phase
REPORT DESIGNER.1 — DB Schema, Layout Standard, Zod Validation

---

## Core Rules

### Rule 1 — No free-form raw HTML designer
The visual editor must NEVER allow a designer to input raw HTML.
All template content must use approved ERP block types only.
`body_html_en` / `body_html_ar` remain as legacy HTML columns for old templates but are NOT editable in the new visual editor.

### Rule 2 — No PDF-only coordinate editor as primary visual editor
The approved visual editor is **Puck** (drag-and-drop JSON block editor).
Do not introduce any tool that positions elements by absolute mm/pt coordinates as the primary editing experience.

### Rule 3 — All blocks must be controlled ERP blocks
Only block types defined in `REPORT_DESIGNER_BLOCK_TYPES` (from `src/lib/report-designer/constants.ts`) are permitted.
Do not create custom block types without adding them to:
1. `src/lib/report-designer/types.ts` (TypeScript interface)
2. `src/lib/report-designer/layout-schema.ts` (Zod schema)
3. `docs/standards/ERP_REPORT_DESIGNER_VISUAL_TEMPLATE_STANDARD.md` (this standard)

### Rule 4 — All bindings must be allowlisted
All `{{binding}}` placeholders and all `binding:` fields in blocks must be keys of `ERP_BINDING_REGISTRY`.
Unknown bindings fail Zod validation. No arbitrary object paths. No SQL expressions.

Sensitive fields are permanently excluded:
```
salary, iban, bank_account, account_number
passport_number (raw), eid_number (raw)
medical data, insurance details, ocr_text
*_id FKs, created_by, updated_by
api_key, secret, token, service_role
```

### Rule 5 — All layout JSON must pass Zod before save or render
Call `validateSaveLayoutInput()` from `src/lib/report-designer/layout-validation.ts` before every write.
Reject any layout that does not pass. Never save raw unvalidated JSON to the DB.

### Rule 6 — Official renderer remains Executive Ledger
The final rendering pipeline is:
```
ReportDesignerLayoutJson → (mapping layer) → ExecutiveLedgerDocument → renderExecutiveLedgerHtml()
```
Never bypass the Executive Ledger renderer to produce direct HTML output from layout JSON.
Never allow layout JSON to reach `innerHTML` directly on the client.

### Rule 7 — Approved/published templates cannot be edited in place
Before any visual layout save, gate on governance status:
```typescript
const EDITABLE = ["draft", "rejected"];
if (!EDITABLE.includes(template.governance_status)) {
  throw new Error("Cannot edit approved/published template — create a new version");
}
```
This check is in `saveReportTemplateVisualLayout()` and must never be bypassed.

### Rule 8 — Live test mode must be read-only and non-mutating
`runReportDesignerTest()` must NEVER:
- Create public QR links
- Write `report_runs` rows
- Send emails
- Mutate templates
- Bypass sensitive-field redaction

All test mode actions are read-only. Full execution (REPORT DESIGNER.5) must maintain these invariants.

### Rule 9 — Only one sidebar item under Reports: Reports Editor
Do NOT create multiple sidebar items for the visual editor.
The single entry point is `Reports → Reports Editor`.
Use a workspace tab/route to open individual templates.

### Rule 10 — No UUID or SERIAL/BIGSERIAL in new migrations
All new ID columns must be `bigint` references. No UUID, no SERIAL, no BIGSERIAL.
Follow the ERP DB standard exactly.

